when he was sacked on a second-down pass attempt. He stayed in for 
a third-down incompletion, then went to the locker room. When he 
returned his hand was in an ice pack. 
</P>
<P>
	The Cardinals have been beset by injuries throughout the  
preseason. Three players were injured in the first quarter Friday. 
Besides Plummer, defensive tackle Mike Moten sprained his right 
knee and defensive end Thomas Burke pulled his left hamstring. 
