<HEADLINE> Phillies Activate Montgomery </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
	PHILADELPHIA (AP) -- The Philadelphia Phillies activated  
right-hander Steve Montgomery from the 15-day disabled list Friday 
and designated left-hander Jim Poole for assignment. 
</P>
<P>
	Montgomery, on the DL since Aug. 4 with a strained groin, is 1-4  
with a 3.15 ERA in 35 games. 
</P>
<P>
	Poole, who struggled in his specialty role against left-handed  
hitters, apologized to manager Terry Francona for not pitching 
better before leaving the clubhouse. The Phillies have 10 days to 
trade him, release him or send him outright to the minors. Poole 
was 1-1 with a 4.33 ERA and allowed 48 hits in 35 1-3 innings. 
</P>
