<HEADLINE> FBI Confirms Sheik Assault Probe </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
	NEW YORK (AP) -- The FBI is investigating allegations that a  
prison guard cursed and assaulted Sheik Omar Abdel-Rahman, the 
imprisoned Egyptian cleric whose followers blew up the World Trade 
Center, officials said Friday. 
</P>
<P>
	The blind sheik was allegedly knocked off the toilet by a prison  
lieutenant who entered his cell early on Aug. 8 at the Federal 
Medical Center in Rochester, Minn., bumping his head and bruising 
his arm. 
</P>
<P>
	The FBI was investigating the assault, said spokesman Paul  
McCabe in Minneapolis. 
</P>
<P>
	The 61-year-old cleric is in declining health with diabetes and  
heart disease, said his attorney, Ramsey Clark. 
</P>
<P>
	Abdel-Rahman was sentenced to life in prison after he was  
convicted in 1995 for conspiracy for allegedly plotting to 
assassinate Egyptian President Hosni Mubarak and approving bombings 
of the United Nations, FBI headquarters in Manhattan and two 
tunnels and a bridge connecting New Jersey to Manhattan. 
  	   	
</P>
</TEXT>
