<HEADLINE> Wood Cleaner Recalled </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
	WASHINGTON (AP) -- About 2,500 bottles of WeatherMate Exterior  
Wood Cleaner have been recalled because the nozzle may be defective 
and injure customers. 
</P>
<P>
	The bottle's nozzle can become brittle and break, the Consumer  
Product Safety Commission said Thursday. If exposed to the cleaner, 
consumers' eyes or hands could become irritated or burned. 
</P>
<P>
	The 32-oz. bottles of cleaner -- made by GE Silicones of  
Waterford, N.Y. -- were sold at hardware stores for $10 to $12 from 
March to May. The cleaner also was sold as part of a $30 kit. 
</P>
<P>
	No injuries have been reported.  
</P>
<P>
	Customers should return the cleaner to the store where they  
bought it for a bottle with a redesigned nozzle. 
  	   	
</P>
</TEXT>
