<HEADLINE> Brewers Grissom, Lefebvre Ejected </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
	MILWAUKEE (AP) -- Brewers outfielder Marquis Grissom and manager  
Jim Lefebvre were ejected from Milwaukee's game with the San 
Francisco Giants on Friday night. 
</P>
<P>
	Grissom took a called third strike in the bottom of the eighth  
inning and briefly argued with home plate umpire Bob Davidson. When 
he reached the dugout, Grissom apparently threw ice from a cooler 
onto the field, and Davidson ejected him. 
</P>
<P>
	Lefebvre and Grissom ran out to argue with Davidson, and  
Lefebvre was quickly ejected. 
</P>
<P>
	Lefebvre pointed and argued vehemently with Davidson, while  
third-base coach Doug Mansolino, shortstop Jose Valentin and 
catcher Bobby Hughes had to restrain Grissom from approaching 
Davidson. After five minutes, Lefebvre and Grissom left the field. 
</P>
<P>
	Milwaukee trailed San Francisco 8-3 at the time of the  
ejections. 
  	   	
</P>
