<BODY>
<CATEGORY> sports </CATEGORY>
<HEADLINE>  Sosa Takes Lead With 49th Homer </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
	CHICAGO (AP) -- Sammy Sosa took over the major league home run  
lead from Mark McGwire on Friday, hitting his 48th and 49th homers 
off Colorado's Pedro Astacio. 
</P>
<P>
	Sosa hit a solo shot in the third to tie McGwire and then passed  
him with another solo drive in the sixth. He has three homers this 
season off Astacio. 
</P>
<P>
	Sosa has hit 151 homers since the start of the 1997 season. He  
is the fifth player in major league history to reach 150 homers 
during a three-year span, joining McGwire, Babe Ruth, Ken Griffey 
Jr., and Jimmie Foxx. 
</P>
<P>
	Sosa is ahead of his 66-homer pace of a year ago when he fell  
four short of McGwire. He didn't hit his 49th homer last season 
until the 128th game. Friday's game was the Cubs' 120th this 
season. 
</P>
<P>
	Sosa's first homer followed one by Mark Grace, the fifth time  
this season the Cubs have homered back-to-back. 
  	   	
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
