<CATEGORY> entertainment </CATEGORY>
<HEADLINE> NBC May Buy Stake in Paxson </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
	NEW YORK (AP) -- NBC is reportedly negotiating a deal to buy part  
of Paxson Communications Corp., which owns or operates 73 
television stations across the country. 
</P>
<P>
	The talks focus on NBC buying 32 percent of Paxson, the Wall  
Street Journal reported Friday, citing unidentified sources 
familiar with the negotiations. The move would be worth more than 
$300 million at current stock values. 
</P>
<P>
	A spokeswoman for NBC declined to comment Friday when contacted  
by The Associated Press. Paxson officials did not immediately 
return phone calls. 
</P>
<P>
	Last week, Paxson said it had hired Salomon Smith Barney to  
explore its options following a landmark Federal Communications 
Commission decision that allows a single company to own more than 
one TV station in a local market. 
</P>
<P>
	That decision was expected to ignite a flurry of dealmaking as  
powerful TV networks make acquisitions, seeking greater dominance 
over major cities around the country. 
</P>
<P>
	Launched last year, Paxson's PAX TV has a presence in the  
nation's top 20 markets but has been struggling to find an audience 
for its rerun-heavy programming, often attracting less than 1 
million of the 100 million households it reaches. 
</P>
<P>
	Paxson had lobbied to relax the ownership rules saying that they  
were needed for broadcasters who face new competition from cable 
stations, satellite TV operators and the Internet. 

  	   	
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
