<HEADLINE> Quantum Corp. To Cut 800 Jobs </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
	MILPITAS, Calif. (AP) -- Computer disk drive and storage drive  
maker Quantum Corp. is eliminating 800 jobs -- about 13 percent of 
its work force -- to better compete in the rapidly growing low-cost 
computer market. 
</P>
<P>
	Quantum will record a special charge of $50 million for its  
second quarter ending Sept. 26 as part of a restructuring of its 
desktop hard disk drive business, the company said Thursday. 
</P>
<P>
	The company plans to lay off 650 to 700 employees at its  
headquarters in Milpitas, Calif. and Dundalk, Ireland over the next 
year. 
</P>
<P>
	Quantum also said it's consolidating the development of some of  
its products, resulting in the immediate loss of 115 jobs. 
  	   	
</P>
</TEXT>
