<HEADLINE> Nebraska Receiver Wiggins Arrested </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
	LINCOLN, Neb. (AP) -- Nebraska senior receiver Shevin Wiggins was  
arrested and charged Friday with sexual assault of a child for 
allegedly fondling two 14-year-old girls, Lancaster County Attorney 
Gary Lacey said. 
</P>
<P>
	Wiggins, 24, and another man, Floyd Brown, 22, are accused of  
touching the girls between July 25 and July 26, at a Lincoln home. 
</P>
<P>
	Wiggins and Brown both were arraigned in Lancaster County Court,  
where their bonds were set at $10,000. Wiggins appeared voluntarily 
with his attorney, while Brown was arrested at his home. 
</P>
<P>
	Wiggins, who was granted a sixth year of eligibility by the NCAA  
in April, remained in jail late Friday afternoon. 
</P>
<P>
	Nebraska coach Frank Solich said Wiggins will be suspended from  
the team until the facts of the case are clear. Solich said Wiggins 
will not be allowed to practice or play in any games until the 
suspension is lifted. 
</P>
<P>
	``It's unfortunate certainly for Shevin and all of us,'' Solich  
said Friday. His arrest ``shocked us all, but we'll just have to 
move forward.'' 
</P>
<P>
	Sexual assault of a child is a felony punishable up to 5 years  
in prison and a $10,000 fine. 
</P>
<P>
	Wiggins, who is also a kick returner, was recruited in 1994 but  
sat out while gaining academic eligibility. He redshirted in 1995 
and played the last three years. 
</P>
<P>
	He is best known for when his kicked ball at the goal line fell  
into the arms of teammate Matt Davison as the Cornhuskers rallied 
to beat Missouri in 1997. 
  	   	
</P>
</TEXT>
