<CATEGORY> weather </CATEGORY>
<HEADLINE> The Nation's Weather  </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
	Showers and thunderstorms rolled across the mid-Atlantic region  
Friday, with scattered showers elsewhere. 
</P>
<P>
	Rain and storms stretched from the Carolinas to Georgia and the  
Florida coast. Rain also drenched western and central New York into 
Pennsylvania, Maryland and Delaware. 
</P>
<P>
	A large area of high pressure hung over the Midwest, bringing  
clear to partly cloudy skies across most of the nation's 
midsection. A trough of low pressure in the northern Plains 
produced some showers and thunderstorms in North Dakota and south 
into central Kansas. 
</P>
<P>
	Fair and dry weather prevailed in the southern Plains.  
</P>
<P>
	In the West, showers were scattered in Colorado, southern Utah,  
New Mexico and Arizona. The rain extended into southern parts of 
Utah and California. The rest of the West Coast was dry. 
</P>
<P>
	The afternoon high in the Lower 48 was 100 degrees in Laughlin,  
Texas. The low was 39 degrees in Marquette, Mich. 
  	   	
</P>
</TEXT>
