<HEADLINE> TWA Extends Contract With Partner </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
	ST. LOUIS (AP) -- Trans World Airlines Inc. is extending the  
contract of its regional partner, but with provisions aimed at 
improving customer service and on-time rates. 
</P>
<P>
	The new, five-year agreement with Trans States Airlines Inc.,  
which operates as Trans World Express at Lambert Airport, includes 
a compensation plan that rewards Trans States for outstanding 
performance and punishes it for substandard results. 
</P>
<P>
	Officials with Trans States say they're up to the challenge.  
</P>
<P>
	``With our new agreement in place, Trans States is ready to  
redouble its efforts to provide the highest levels of customer 
satisfaction in our product class,'' said marketing director 
William Mishk. 
</P>
<P>
	Trans States shuttles passengers to TWA's St. Louis hub from 24  
cities in the Midwest, Southeast and other regions. 
</P>
<P>
	Both airlines are based in St. Louis.  

  	   	
