<HEADLINE> Seward Becomes Paris News Editor </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
	PARIS (AP) -- Deborah Seward, who has reported for The Associated  
Press from Europe and Russia, has been promoted to news editor in 
Paris. 
</P>
<P>
	The appointment was announced today by Paris Chief of Bureau  
Abner Katzman. 
</P>
<P>
	Seward began her AP career in 1988 in Warsaw and was assigned to  
Berlin the following year. Following a brief stint on the 
International Desk in New York, she transferred to Moscow in 1991. 
She became news editor there in 1994, and has been in Paris since 
1997. 
  	   	
</P>
</TEXT>
