<CATEGORY> sports </CATEGORY>
<HEADLINE>  Liberty 72, Rockers 55 </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
	NEW YORK (AP) -- Becky Hammon scored 16 points as the New York  
Liberty romped over the Cleveland Rockers 72-55 on Thursday night. 
</P>
<P>
	Sophia Witherspoon added 15 for the Liberty, who learned of the  
death of Houston Comet guard Kim Perrot before the game. Her death 
was announced to the crowd of 16,782, who stood for a moment of 
silence at Madison Square Garden after a video tribute to Perrot. 
</P>
<P>
	The Liberty, many of whom were crying at the start of the game,  
raced out to a 24-11 lead and never trailed. 
</P>
<P>
	Merlakia Jones had 14 for the Rockers (6-25), who have lost a  
franchise-high eight consecutive games. 
</P>
<P>
	Crystal Robinson added 11 for the Liberty (18-13), who clinched  
the Eastern Conference regular-season title with a victory over 
Washington on Tuesday. New York earned a first-round bye and 
homecourt advantage in the playoffs, which begin Tuesday. 
</P>
<P>
	The Liberty, winners of five of their last seven games, visits  
Cleveland in the final game of the season on Saturday. 
</P>
<P>
	Trailing 40-21 at halftime, Cleveland came within 47-37 with  
13:05 remaining. New York went on a 13-3 run, capped by three 
consecutive 3-pointers by Sophia Witherspoon, for a 60-40 lead with 
9:39 remaining. 
</P>
<P>
	Rockers guard Michelle Edwards sprained her left ankle in the  
second half and was carried off the floor by her teammates. Teresa 
Weatherspoon left the game early in the first half with a sprained 
left thumb. 
</P>
<P>
	Cleveland has the league's worst record after winning the  
Eastern Conference title last season. The Rockers have struggled 
without leading scorer and rebounder Isabelle Fijalkowski, who 
chose not to play in the WNBA this summer. 
</P>
<P>
	The Rockers lost by 27 points in the season opener at Madison  
Square Garden on June 10. Rebecca Lobo suffered a season-ending 
knee injury 42 seconds into the game. 
  	   	
</P>
</TEXT>
