<CATEGORY> entertainment </CATEGORY>
<HEADLINE> Cruise, Kidman Aid Scottish Theater </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
	DUNDEE, Scotland (AP) -- Tom Cruise and Nicole Kidman are lending  
their names to a campaign to help pay for a full-time troupe for a 
small Scottish theater. 
</P>
<P>
	The artistic director of the Dundee Repertory Theater is Hamish  
Glen, the brother of Iain Glen, Ms. Kidman's co-star last year in 
the London and New York theatrical productions of ``The Blue 
Room.'' 
</P>
<P>
	``Hamish got on very well with Nicole and Tom and he decided to  
write to them to see if they'd help out,'' Nicola Young, a 
spokeswoman for the theater, said Friday. 
</P>
<P>
	``We got a phone call from Ms. Kidman in Australia saying she  
and Tom would be delighted to get involved with the theater and 
lend their names to the campaign,'' Ms. Young said. ``Nicole 
started out in theaters in Australia and she recognizes how 
important they are to communities and to the acting profession.'' 
</P>
<P>
	Ms. Young said the couple would be invited to take part in a  
fund-raising dinner in Dundee early next year. 
  	   	
</P>
</TEXT>
