<HEADLINE> Cardinals QB Plummer Injured </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
	TEMPE, Ariz. (AP) -- Quarterback Jake Plummer sprained his right  
thumb on Arizona's first possession of Friday night's exhibition 
game against the Tennessee Titans. 
</P>
<P>
	Plummer went to the locker room for X-rays, which were negative,  
and returned to watch from the sideline with his hand in ice. Team 
officials said he would not play the rest of the game, but the 
injury was not believed to be serious. 
</P>
<P>
	He was replaced by backup Dave Brown.  
</P>
<P>
	Plummer, considered one of the NFL's rising stars, was injured  
on a second-down pass attempt. He stayed in for a third-down 
incompletion, then went to the locker room. When he returned his 
hand was in an ice pack. 
</P>
<P>
	The Cardinals have been beset by injuries throughout the  
preseason. Three players were injured in the first quarter Friday. 
Besides Plummer, defensive tackle Mike Moten sprained his right 
knee and defensive end Thomas Burke pulled his left hamstring. 
</P>
<P>
	On Monday, three linemen were injured in an auto accident on the  
way to a morning team meeting. 
  	   	
