<HEADLINE> Dollar Mixed, Gold Down in Europe </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
	LONDON (AP) -- The U.S. dollar was mixed against other major  
currencies in European trading today. Gold prices fell. 
</P>
<P>
	The euro was quoted at $1.0666 in late European trading, up from  
$1.0602 Thursday. Later, in midday trading in New York, the euro 
traded at $1.0648 
</P>
<P>
	Other dollar rates in Europe, compared with late Thursday,  
included 111.11 Japanese yen, down from 111.44; 1.4967 Swiss 
francs, down from 1.5070; 1.4946 Canadian dollars, up from 1.4866. 
</P>
<P>
	The British pound was quoted at $1.6175, up from $1.6115.  
</P>
<P>
	In midday trading in New York, the dollar bought 111.32 yen, and  
the pound was worth $1.6140. 
</P>
<P>
	Currencies of the 11 countries participating in the euro are no  
longer traded separately, though they remain in use. Based on euro 
rates, the dollar is worth 1.8337 German marks, down from 1.8448; 
6.1500 French francs, down from 6.1871; 2.0661 Dutch guilders, down 
from 2.0786; 1,815.37 Italian lire, down from 1,826.33. 
</P>
<P>
	Gold closed in London at $258.20 bid per troy ounce, down from  
$258.30 on Thursday. In Zurich the bid price was $257.95, down from 
$258.10. Gold fell $1.10 in Hong Kong to close at $259.65. 
</P>
<P>
	Silver closed in London at $5.19 bid per troy ounce, up from  
$5.16. 
  	   	
</P>
