<P>
	Dow Closes Up 136.77 at 11,100.61  
</P>
<P>
	NEW YORK (AP) -- Blue-chip stocks ended the week with a solid  
rally even as the prospect of an increase in interest rates next 
Tuesday kept many investors out of the market. At the close of 
trading Friday on Wall Street, the Dow Jones industrial average was 
up 136.77 at 11,100.61. The Dow gained 126.96 points for the week, 
or 1.2 percent. Broader stock indicators were also higher today, 
although their gains were more modest. Investors today gravitated 
toward a handful of blue-chip stocks, seeking safe bets in case 
interest rates continue to rise, analysts said. 

</P>
