<CATEGORY> usa </CATEGORY>
<HEADLINE> Dallas Names 1st Black Police Chief </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
	DALLAS (AP) -- Dallas hired its first black police chief Friday,  
promoting an assistant chief and 19-year veteran of the force. 
</P>
<P>
	Assistant chief Terrell Bolton, 40, will become the city's top  
law enforcement officer on Sept. 30 when the current chief retires. 
</P>
<P>
	Bolton said that being named the first black chief feels ``very  
good,'' but added: ``I don't get a lot of joy that it's taken so 
long.'' 
</P>
<P>
	Chief Ben Click said while it was important to have a black man  
run the city's police department, Bolton was the most qualified of 
the candidates. 
</P>
<P>
	``I don't see Chief Bolton as an African American. I see him as  
an extremely talented individual,'' Click said. 
</P>
<P>
	Bolton joined the force in 1980 and now commands half the  
department's six patrol divisions. 
  	   	
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
