<HEADLINE> Suspended UC Player Was Arrested </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
	CINCINNATI (AP) -- Sophomore forward Eugene Land was arrested for  
shoplifting on Tuesday night, two days before the University of 
Cincinnati suspended him for unspecified reasons. 
</P>
<P>
	Land, a 6-foot-8 backup from Cincinnati, is scheduled to appear  
in Hamilton County Municipal Court on Aug. 31. 
</P>
<P>
	The sheriff's department said Land was observed selecting  
merchandise from a display at a department store and placing it in 
a shopping bag. He was stopped by security as he left the store. 
</P>
<P>
	The Cincinnati Post reported that Land was found to have about  
$256 in merchandise. 
</P>
<P>
	Coach Bob Huggins suspended Land on Thursday, but declined to  
give a reason. He would not comment on the arrest. 
</P>
<P>
	Land will remain on athletic scholarship during the fall  
quarter, but will not participate in conditioning, practice or any 
basketball activities. Land could be reinstated for the winter 
quarter, Huggins said. 
</P>
<P>
	Land averaged 3.2 points and 1.7 rebounds for the Bearcats last  
season. 
</P>
