<HEADLINE> Tigers Activate Jefferies From DL </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
	DETROIT (AP) -- Gregg Jefferies was activated Friday from the  
15-day disabled list by the Detroit Tigers, who optioned Gabe 
Alvarez to Triple-A Toledo. 
</P>
<P>
	Jefferies, 31, had been on the disabled list since Aug. 3 with a  
strained right hamstring. Before the injury, he was hitting .204 
with six home runs and 18 RBI. 
</P>
<P>
	He was sidelined with a bruised right elbow in June.  
</P>
<P>
	Alvarez, 25, started the season at Toledo and was recalled July  
24 after outfielder Bobby Higginson was placed on the disabled list 
with a sprained toe. 
</P>
<P>
	In 15 games this season for the Tigers -- 10 of them as starter --  
Alvarez hit .190 with three homers and two RBIs. 
</P>
