</P>
<P>
	DHAKA, Bangladesh (AP) -- Abdus Salam Talukder, an opposition  
leader who was stricken with a heart attack earlier this week, died 
Friday, minutes before he was to take a flight for treatment 
abroad, party officials said. He was 64. 
</P>
<P>
	Talukder was a member of the central policy- making body of the  
Bangladesh Nationalist Party and a minister in the Cabinet of 
former Prime Minister Khaleda Zia, who now heads the opposition. 
</P>
<P>
	Talukder had a heart attack on Aug. 15.  

