                          *Fred M. Thrower    	
</P>
<P>
	GREENWICH, Conn. (AP) -- Fred M. Thrower, a longtime manager of  
WPIX-TV in New York, died Aug. 16. He was 89. 
</P>
<P>
	Thrower's television career spanned 46 years. He became general  
sales manager of ABC in 1942 and president in charge of sales for 
CBS in 1951, and joined WPIX in 1953. 
</P>
<P>
	In 1971, he received the Crystal Award from the National  
Hemophilia Association, of which he was a trustee. He served as 
first vice president of Americans for Children Relief. 
</P>
<P>
	He is survived by a son and a daughter.  
  	   	
