<HEADLINE> Brothers Suspected in Gay Arson Case </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
	SACRAMENTO, Calif. (AP) -- Two brothers suspected of killing a  
gay couple and setting a series of synagogue fires are also under 
suspicion in an abortion clinic blaze, The Sacramento Bee reported 
today. 
</P>
<P>
	Evidence found at the home, storage locker and vehicle belonging  
to Benjamin Williams, 31, and James Matthews, 29, may link them to 
the June 25 clinic fire, the newspaper reported, citing 
unidentified sources. 
</P>
<P>
	The fire damaged the Country Club Medical Center, but not the  
clinic. The blaze had earlier been examined for links to fires at 
three Sacramento-area synagogues in June that caused $1 million in 
damage. 
</P>
<P>
	No charges have been filed in the fires.  
</P>
<P>
	Both men have pleaded innocent in the July 1 slayings of Gary  
Matson, 50, and Winfield Mowder, 40, who were shot at their home. 
</P>
<P>
	Authorities also have reportedly linked the brothers to the  
World Church of the Creator, an Illinois-based white supremacist 
group. 
  	   	
</P>
</TEXT>
