<HEADLINE> Elizabeth Taylor Hospitalized </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
	LOS ANGELES (AP) -- Elizabeth Taylor was hospitalized after  
breaking a bone in her back during a fall. 
</P>
<P>
	The actress fell in her Bel Air home on Thursday night and was  
later admitted to Cedars-Sinai Medical Center, her publicist said 
in a statement released Friday. 
</P>
<P>
	``As a result of the fall, Miss Taylor sustained a compressive  
fracture of the 12th thoracic vertebra,'' neurosurgeon Dr. Patrick 
Rhoten said in the statement. ``She is in no danger from a 
neurological viewpoint and she is resting comfortably.'' 
</P>
<P>
	She will need four to five weeks to recuperate, the statement  
said. 
</P>
<P>
	Miss Taylor, 67, has been bothered with health problems in  
recent years, including a broken back last year and lengthy 
recuperation from hip surgeries. She also had brain surgery in 1997 
to remove a benign tumor. 
</P>
<P>
	Many of her back problems have been traced to 1945 when she hurt  
her back falling off a horse during the filming of ``National 
Velvet.'' 
</P>
<P>
	The actress won Academy Awards for her roles in ``Butterfield  
8'' in 1960 and ``Who's Afraid of Virginia Woolf?'' in 1966. 
</P>
<P>
	She has appeared in few projects in recent years, but has spent  
much time raising money and awareness for AIDS causes and launching 
new perfumes. 
  	   	
</P>
</TEXT>
